The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Briefs
                                                                                                               SPORTS BRIEFS
                  
	 Bethesda (Maryland): Tiger Woods sent Roger Federer a congratulatory text message Sunday after the Swiss won his record 15th Grand Slam title at Wimbledon and then went on to win the AT amp;T National tournament.Woods said he sent the simple message great job. Now its my turn, before he teed off. Tournament host Woods fired a three-under-par 67 to finish at 13-under 267, one stroke better than Mahan whose sizzling final round 62 had lifted him to the top of the leaderboard.         
	 Liverpool: Yossi Benayoun has signed a new Liverpool contract, committing him to the Premier League club until 2013.         
	New Delhi: Calcutta giants East Bengal and Mohun Bagan could be two of the teams taking part in the Bangabandhu Gold Cup to be held in Dhaka later this year. The Bangladesh Football Federation is planning to host an eight-team tournament with a prize purse of $1.5 million and is keen to invite Bagan and East Bengal besides a team each from Uzbekistan, Thailand, Qatar and the UAE.        
	 Newport: Prakash Amritraj got off to a flying start at the Campbell Hall of Fame Tennis Championships when he defeated Danai Udomchoke of Thailand 6-1, 6-4 on Monday to progress to the second round.         
	 London: Wimbledon runner-up Andy Roddick withdrew Monday from the US Davis Cup teams quarter final at Croatia, citing a right hip flexor injury. He lost to Roger Federer in the final at Wimbledon .        
	 Calcutta: Akram Khan thrashed Vishal Shay 3-0 in the opening round of the Senior State Billiards Championship on Monday. Defending Champion Brijesh Damani also won 3-0 against Jyotirmoy Das.                                                                                                                                                                       
